==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Losenger
<hw>Los"en*ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>losengier</ets>, <ets>losengeor</ets>, fr. <ets>losengier</ets> to
deceive, flatter, <ets>losenge</ets>, flattery, Pr. <ets>lauzenga</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>laus</ets> praise. Cf. <er>Lozenge</er>.]</ety> <def>A
flatterer; a deceiver; a cozener.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To a fair pair of gallows, there to end their lives with shame, as
a number of such other <qex>losengers</qex> had done.</q>
<rj><qau>Holinshed.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Losengerie</ent>⟦br⟧
